		<title>Contact forms</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/contact-forms/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2015 14:16:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://welfare.cmsmasters.net/?page_id=163</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="dc94fd4151" data_padding_top="60" data_color="default" data_bot_style="default" data_top_style="default" data_width="boxed"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="48491b620f" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_heading shortcode_id="81bfb905cf" type="h2" font_weight="normal" font_style="normal" text_align="left" margin_top="10" margin_bottom="30" animation_delay="0"]Form Builder[/cmsmasters_heading][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="898d84ba19" animation_delay="0"]

A powerful <strong>Form Builder Tool</strong>, customly developed by CMSMasters, lets you create an <strong>unlimited amount of forms</strong> of different types and complexity, from simple <strong>contact forms</strong> to<strong>complex questionnaires</strong> with numerous fields, radio-buttons, checkboxes and dropdowns, text areas, as well as set validation for these fields. You can decide how to arrange fields. Activate Captcha and even select how received message will look like with Message Composer.

[/cmsmasters_text][cmsmasters_divider shortcode_id="898315f432" width="long" height="1" style="solid" position="center" margin_top="50" margin_bottom="65" animation_delay="0"][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row][cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="9e7895f7b4" data_padding_bottom="80" data_padding_top="0" data_color="default" data_bot_style="default" data_top_style="default" data_width="boxed"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="1b8973a95f" data_width="1/2"][cmsmasters_heading shortcode_id="1540c916ec" type="h2" font_weight="normal" font_style="normal" text_align="left" margin_top="0" margin_bottom="30" animation_delay="0"]Simple Form[/cmsmasters_heading][cmsmasters_contact_form shortcode_id="8c3885d804" form_plugin="cfb" form_cfb="164" email_cfb="example@domain.com" animation_delay="0"][/cmsmasters_column][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="b2ad4b56f3" data_width="1/2"][cmsmasters_heading shortcode_id="29cb86aaf8" type="h2" font_weight="normal" font_style="normal" text_align="left" margin_top="0" margin_bottom="30" animation_delay="0"]Questionnaire Form[/cmsmasters_heading][cmsmasters_contact_form shortcode_id="b4c0271041" form_plugin="cfb" form_cfb="710" email_cfb="example@domain.com" animation_delay="0"][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

<p style="text-align: center;">Custom HTML, CSS and JS are powerful instruments for experienced developers, who’d like to add their own code, styles or scripts directly to the certain page.</p>

Nam porta leo ut felis suscipit, vel semper lectus vehicula. Nulla vitae porta leo. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. Fusce bibendum arcu in lacinia condimentum. Aenean id nunc quis ex congue facilisis. Proin non tempus arcu. Donec dictum elementum ex et aliquet. Praesent at pulvinar augue, ut ultricies mauris. Nulla congue nulla in semper cursus. Sed auctor condimentum sem a tincidunt. Duis rhoncus maximus varius. Nullam imperdiet imperdiet massa vel lacinia. Nam auctor odio velit, at ultricies nisi dictum quis. Vestibulum tempus tellus nec leo malesuada, in tempus quam vehicula.

Sed nec blandit nibh. Pellentesque commodo suscipit gravida. Sed sit amet ex sed mi dignissim elementum in ut quam. Vivamus laoreet non mauris eget mattis. Nam turpis orci, consectetur vel accumsan sed, condimentum at sapien. Nunc ut egestas neque, eu hendrerit lacus. Suspendisse fermentum congue dui nec fringilla. Duis volutpat nunc lectus. 		<title>Full Irish Breakfast In Manhattan</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/2017/05/13/full-irish-breakfast-in-manhattan/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 13 May 2017 09:38:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://welfare.cmsmasters.net/?p=103</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed ultrices ipsum non mattis pharetra. Integer laoreet non felis sit amet pharetra. Integer mollis eget felis non finibus. Nullam nibh mauris, fermentum vitae felis vehicula, aliquam bibendum sapien. In euismod velit vitae neque rhoncus congue. Aliquam luctus, sapien in consectetur cursus, quam urna euismod magna, sed pellentesque massa libero eu lorem. Aenean rhoncus gravida nisl vel pretium. Nam ac nisl non ipsum vestibulum vehicula vulputate sagittis magna. Aenean est nisl, convallis volutpat tempor ac, tempus ac ante. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. Fusce rhoncus sodales tempor. Nunc pretium tortor felis, eget cursus magna accumsan a.

Etiam eu molestie eros, commodo hendrerit sapien. Maecenas tempus leo ac nisi iaculis porta. Sed sapien tortor, aliquet a velit ut, lacinia molestie velit. Maecenas ornare consequat massa ullamcorper dapibus. Aliquam auctor, sapien sit amet accumsan facilisis, enim enim aliquet arcu, tincidunt pellentesque justo turpis id neque. Duis eleifend nunc sit amet mi dapibus ornare. Suspendisse vel libero sem.]]></content:encoded>

Integer mollis eget felis non finibus. Nullam nibh mauris, fermentum vitae felis vehicula, aliquam bibendum sapien. In euismod velit vitae neque rhoncus congue. Aliquam luctus, sapien in consectetur cursus, quam urna euismod magna, sed pellentesque massa libero eu lorem. Aenean rhoncus gravida nisl vel pretium. Nam ac nisl non ipsum vestibulum vehicula vulputate sagittis magna. Aenean est nisl, convallis volutpat tempor ac, tempus ac ante. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. Fusce rhoncus sodales tempor. Nunc pretium tortor felis, eget cursus magna accumsan a.

Etiam eu molestie eros, commodo hendrerit sapien. Maecenas tempus leo ac nisi iaculis porta. Sed sapien tortor, aliquet a velit ut, lacinia molestie velit. Maecenas ornare consequat massa ullamcorper dapibus. Aliquam auctor, sapien sit amet accumsan facilisis, enim enim aliquet arcu, tincidunt pellentesque justo turpis id neque. Duis eleifend nunc sit amet mi dapibus ornare. Suspendisse vel libero sem.]]></content:encoded>

<ul>
 	<li>Cras sodales nisi pretium placerat tempus.</li>
 	<li>Pellentesque id erat sodales, mollis turpis sed, bibendum justo.</li>
 	<li>Nunc condimentum tortor non fringilla congue.</li>
 	<li>Donec tempus odio eu libero mattis, in posuere nisl vulputate.</li>
</ul>
Imperdiet mi. Suspendisse mollis leo in sapien venenatis, ac congue ex auctor. Donec dapibus ipsum ex, eu fringilla arcu elementum at. Nulla quis urna pharetra, tincidunt sem a, pharetra mauris. Duis vel posuere tortor. Integer at porttitor quam. Sed consequat nec dui ut feugiat. Phasellus feugiat non ante a lacinia. Sed accumsan magna eu dapibus tempus. Etiam euismod nulla sed ex ultrices gravida.

Sed nec blandit nibh. Pellentesque commodo suscipit gravida. Sed sit amet ex sed mi dignissim elementum in ut quam. Vivamus laoreet non mauris eget mattis. Nam turpis orci, consectetur vel accumsan sed, condimentum at sapien. Nunc ut egestas neque, eu hendrerit lacus. Suspendisse fermentum congue dui nec fringilla. Duis volutpat nunc lectus. Suspendisse potenti. Suspendisse egestas venenatis nunc. Donec at laoreet lacus.

Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed ultrices ipsum non mattis pharetra. Integer laoreet non felis sit amet pharetra. Integer mollis eget felis non finibus. Nullam nibh mauris, fermentum vitae felis vehicula, aliquam bibendum sapien. In euismod velit vitae neque rhoncus congue. Aliquam luctus, sapien in consectetur cursus, quam urna euismod magna, sed pellentesque massa libero eu lorem. Aenean rhoncus gravida nisl vel pretium. Nam ac nisl non ipsum vestibulum vehicula vulputate sagittis magna. Aenean est nisl, convallis volutpat tempor ac, tempus ac ante. Class aptent taciti sociosqu ad litora torquent per conubia nostra, per inceptos himenaeos. Fusce rhoncus sodales tempor. Nunc pretium tortor felis, eget cursus magna accumsan a.

<h2>Blockquotes</h2>
Single line blockquote:
<blockquote>Stay hungry. Stay foolish.</blockquote>
Multi line blockquote with a cite reference:
<blockquote>People think focus means saying yes to the thing you've got to focus on. But that's not what it means at all. It means saying no to the hundred other good ideas that there are. You have to pick carefully. I'm actually as proud of the things we haven't done as the things I have done. Innovation is saying no to 1,000 things. <cite>Steve Jobs - Apple Worldwide Developers' Conference, 1997</cite></blockquote>

<h2>HTML Tags</h2>
These supported tags come from the WordPress.com code <a title="Code" href="http://en.support.wordpress.com/code/">FAQ</a>.

<strong>Address Tag</strong>

<address>1 Infinite Loop
Cupertino, CA 95014
United States</address><strong>Anchor Tag (aka. Link)</strong>

This is an example of a <a title="Apple" href="http://apple.com">link</a>.

<strong>Abbreviation Tag</strong>

The abbreviation <abbr title="Seriously">srsly</abbr> stands for "seriously".

<strong>Acronym Tag</strong>

The acronym <acronym title="For The Win">ftw</acronym> stands for "for the win".

<strong>Big Tag</strong>

These tests are a <big>big</big> deal, but this tag is no longer supported in HTML5.

<strong>Cite Tag</strong>

"Code is poetry." --<cite>Automattic</cite>

<strong>Code Tag</strong>

You will learn later on in these tests that <code>word-wrap: break-word;</code> will be your best friend.<!--more-->

<strong>Delete Tag</strong>

This tag will let you <del>strikeout text</del>, but this tag is no longer supported in HTML5 (use the <code>&lt;strike&gt;</code> instead).

<strong>Emphasize Tag</strong>

The emphasize tag should <em>italicize</em> text.

<strong>Insert Tag</strong>

This tag should denote <ins>inserted</ins> text.

<strong>Keyboard Tag</strong>

This scarcely known tag emulates <kbd>keyboard text</kbd>, which is usually styled like the <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> tag.

<strong>Preformatted Tag</strong>

This tag styles large blocks of code.
<pre>.post-title {
	margin: 0 0 5px;
	font-weight: bold;
	font-size: 38px;
	line-height: 1.2;
}</pre>
<strong>Quote Tag</strong>

<q>Developers, developers, developers...</q> --Steve Ballmer

<strong>Strong Tag</strong>

This tag shows <strong>bold<strong> text.</strong></strong>

<strong>Subscript Tag</strong>

Getting our science styling on with H<sub>2</sub>O, which should push the "2" down.

<strong>Superscript Tag</strong>

Still sticking with science and Isaac Newton's E = MC<sup>2</sup>, which should lift the 2 up.

<strong>Teletype Tag</strong>

This rarely used tag emulates <tt>teletype text</tt>, which is usually styled like the <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> tag.

<strong>Variable Tag</strong>

This allows you to denote <var>variables</var>.

<strong>Contact Form
</strong>

<blockquote>Your attitude is like a box of crayons that color your world. Constantly color your picture gray, and your picture will always be bleak. Try adding some bright colors to the picture by including humor, and your picture begins to lighten up.</blockquote>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Terms and Conditions are a set of rules and guidelines that a user must agree to in order to use your website or mobile app. It acts as a legal contract between you (the company) who has the website or mobile app and the user who access your website and mobile app.

It’s up to you to set the rules and guidelines that the user must agree to. You can think of your Terms and Conditions agreement as the legal agreement where you maintain your rights to exclude users from your app in the event that they abuse your app, and where you maintain your legal rights against potential app abusers, and so on.

Terms and Conditions are also known as Terms of Service or Terms of Use.

This type of legal agreement can be used for both your website and your mobile app. It’s not required (it’s not recommended actually) to have separate Terms and Conditions agreements: one for your website and one for your mobile app.]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Grill Pan</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/product/grill-pan/</link>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="cb9759f019" data_width="boxed" data_padding_left="3" data_padding_right="3" data_color="default" data_bg_position="top center" data_bg_repeat="no-repeat" data_bg_attachment="scroll" data_bg_size="cover" data_bg_parallax_ratio="0.5" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="50"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="c3b6ff75cd" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="193ca0b0e0" animation_delay="0"]

Maecenas iaculis mauris lacus, nec bibendum tellus maximus non. Proin eget dictum eros, sed viverra diam. Praesent eu rhoncus eros. In hac habitasse platea dictumst. Curabitur sagittis tristique odio eget pharetra. Aenean cursus congue est non dignissim. Ut mattis augue eu purus tristique, vitae fermentum libero sagittis. Etiam euismod magna neque, suscipit lobortis augue porta non. Interdum et malesuada fames ac ante ipsum primis in faucibus. Quisque id ullamcorper ex. Etiam vestibulum felis at leo sodales aliquam. Donec risus nisi, ornare ut nisi non, vulputate dapibus turpis. Vestibulum non rhoncus lacus.
<ul>
 	<li>Donec auctor sapien vel ornare efficitur.</li>
 	<li>Aliquam pellentesque neque sed tortor faucibus, a ullamcorper justo tempor.</li>
 	<li>Vivamus pretium urna vitae interdum mattis.</li>
 	<li>Sed pretium leo eget est aliquam, sed aliquam ligula rhoncus.</li>
 	<li>Nullam sed risus fringilla, porta libero eu, ultrices nulla.</li>
</ul>

		<title>Cutlery Sets</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/product/cutlery-sets/</link>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="2e8dfe01ed"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="3e2ed6ad21" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="2586d957bd"]

Aenean semper varius pellentesque. Quisque ornare ipsum vitae purus semper, ut fermentum sem tempus. Aenean et nibh dui. Vivamus vel dolor sit amet nunc tincidunt congue sit amet nec enim. Phasellus finibus libero eu urna convallis, at fermentum ex mattis. Sed maximus ligula dignissim pretium euismod. Donec semper est eget magna mollis bibendum. Maecenas elit enim, venenatis nec nisl sit amet, scelerisque mattis est. Vivamus luctus volutpat tortor, ac venenatis metus laoreet id. Nam sollicitudin turpis at vestibulum porta. Nulla maximus augue eu felis molestie luctus. Mauris quis mauris a elit mattis congue. Nam at laoreet libero, non aliquet sapien. Nulla at nunc ante.

Suspendisse feugiat metus eget vestibulum aliquam. Vestibulum fringilla vitae orci at egestas. Phasellus molestie ex eget diam accumsan luctus. Sed dapibus metus at aliquam luctus. Mauris turpis nisi, egestas non enim et, gravida rutrum mauris. Aenean sollicitudin pretium urna nec congue. Sed eu metus faucibus, cursus lacus vel, consequat est. Donec nec ipsum quis sapien tincidunt faucibus et at magna. Nullam elementum blandit eros, at molestie justo. Proin venenatis bibendum viverra.
<ul>
 	<li>Vivamus pretium urna vitae interdum mattis.</li>
 	<li>Sed pretium leo eget est aliquam, sed aliquam ligula rhoncus.</li>
 	<li>Nullam sed risus fringilla, porta libero eu, ultrices nulla.</li>
</ul>

Morbi non accumsan libero, volutpat ullamcorper odio. Donec non libero id augue suscipit commodo. Curabitur porta ac ligula vel sollicitudin. Praesent vestibulum tellus urna, in imperdiet neque lobortis eleifend. Nunc eros nulla, porta quis urna nec, luctus viverra diam. In ut ante est. Duis venenatis erat ac nisl malesuada gravida. Pellentesque pellentesque tempor urna, quis vehicula mi mollis hendrerit. Etiam iaculis convallis arcu, id lacinia massa imperdiet vitae.

Nam accumsan a augue ut lobortis. Ut ac libero vel libero consectetur dictum ac in ante. Pellentesque efficitur nibh id condimentum blandit. Phasellus vulputate, tellus in vestibulum feugiat, felis nisl pulvinar mi, mollis eleifend orci risus sit amet orci. Cum sociis natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. Maecenas vitae viverra risus. Vivamus eget accumsan elit, tincidunt pharetra orci. 		<title>Cream Cheese Pound Cake</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/cream-cheese-pound-cake/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 10 Jan 2015 13:22:06 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://construction-pro.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=9410</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="d583ff8dc1" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_width="1/1" data_shortcode_id="7e15a71c2b"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="d7a2a2fba8" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="070e420247" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="f28e906234" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="a083508d0a" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla. Combine the flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon; stir into the creamed mixture. Mix in oats and nuts until just blended. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Cookies should be at least 2 inches apart.";i:2;s:77:"Bake for about 12 minutes in the preheated oven. 	<item>
		<title>Pumpkin Ginger Cupcakes</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/pumpkin-ginger-cupcakes/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 13:21:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13122</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="6b021cdaed" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="b4f4fa8adc" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="d6c1e4a2d2" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Good Food sounds like the name of an amazingly delicious food delivery service, but don't be fooled. The blog is actually a compilation of recipes, cooking videos, and nutrition tips. ]]></excerpt:encoded>

			<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[a:3:{i:0;s:253:"Preheat an oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease 24 muffin cups, or line with paper muffin liners. Whisk together the flour, pudding mix, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ground ginger, allspice, cloves, and crystallized ginger in a bowl; set aside.";i:1;s:425:"Beat the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar with an electric mixer in a large bowl until light and fluffy. The mixture should be noticeably lighter in color. Add the eggs one at a time, allowing each egg to blend into the butter mixture before adding the next. Beat in the vanilla and pumpkin puree with the last egg. Stir in the flour mixture, mixing until just incorporated. Pour the batter into the prepared muffin cups.";i:2;s:187:"Bake in the preheated oven until golden and the tops spring back when lightly pressed, about 20 minutes. Cool in the pans for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely on a wire rack.";}]]></wp:meta_value>

		<title>Cherry Pie</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/cherry-pie/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 13:32:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[backdoor]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13125</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="befcafe7df" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="d8a1cf8c90" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="b6365cf478" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

			<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[a:5:{i:0;s:309:"Cut the shortening into the flour and salt with the whisking blades of a stand mixer until the crumbs are pea-sized. Mix in cold water by hand just until the dough holds together. Divide the dough in half and form it into two disks. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate until chilled through, 30 minutes to 1 hour.";i:1;s:205:"Roll out one disk of dough into a 11-inch circle. Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Refrigerate until needed. Roll out the dough for the top crust, transfer it to a plate or baking sheet, and refrigerate.";i:2;s:94:"Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place a baking tray in the oven to preheat.";i:3;s:529:"Place the cherries, sugar, and cornstarch in a medium-sized non-aluminum saucepan. Allow the mixture to stand for 10 minutes, or until the sugar draws out the cherries' juices. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Lower the heat; simmer for 1 minute, or until the juices thicken and become translucent. Remove pan from heat, and stir in butter and almond extract. Allow the filling to cool to lukewarm. Pour the filling into the pie shell. Cover with top crust, crimp the edges to seal, and cut vents for steam.";i:4;s:177:"Bake in a preheated 375 degree F (190 degree C) oven on the baking tray for 45 to 55 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown. Allow to cool for several hours before slicing.";}]]></wp:meta_value>

		<title>Creamy Mushroom Pasta</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/creamy-mushroom-pasta/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 13:46:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13135</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="0ffa31f182" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="4b4d4525fc" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="4c63479459" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Great Easy Waffles</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/great-easy-waffles/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 13:52:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13142</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="f51c5b3542" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="1d6598b586" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="601be76db2" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="ebd1a1d92c" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="f7920393d4" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="d267c400a2" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Good Old Pancakes</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/good-old-pancakes/</link>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="c9fe550359" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="275f2c15a1" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="5b06580c9e" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Donut Muffins</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/donut-muffins/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 14:21:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13151</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="859319594b" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="dc83a85412" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="9b4a24c736" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Stir in the milk, then mix in the baking powder and flour until just combined. Fill the prepared mini muffin cups about half full.";i:2;s:79:"Bake in the preheated oven until the tops are lightly golden, 15 to 20 minutes.";i:3;s:272:"While muffins are baking, place 1/4 cup of melted margarine in a bowl. In a separate bowl, mix together 1/2 cup of sugar with the cinnamon. Remove muffins from their cups, dip each muffin in the melted margarine, and roll in the sugar-cinnamon mixture. Let cool and serve.";}]]></wp:meta_value>

	<item>
		<title>French Macaroon</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/french-macaroon/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 14:29:28 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13158</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="c1bb231181" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="51727b5f81" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="f8001e0912" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Panna Cotta with Berries</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/panna-cotta-with-berries/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 28 Jun 2017 14:40:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13161</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="da91f0b734" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="c8aaaefd7e" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="f6b0770dfd" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Orange Cake</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/orange-cake/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 12:26:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13164</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="401e8ea539" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="fddd15f009" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="1c8c3753c7" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Brontosaurus Burgers</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/brontosaurus-burgers/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 12:42:03 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13169</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="26c115fc72" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="8adc4fb346" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="cfc4190571" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Lightly mix in the ground chuck, ground sirloin, onion soup mix, Worcestershire sauce, steak seasoning sauce, hot sauce, and salt and pepper. Form the meat mixture into 6 large patties, 6 inches across by 1 inch thick.";i:2;s:335:"Place the burgers on the preheated grill, and cook 10 to 15 minutes per side, until the burgers are browned and no longer pink in the middle. Brush each burger with barbecue sauce, flip them and grill for 5 minutes to slightly char the sauce. 		<title>Moroccan Shabbat Fish</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/moroccan-shabbat-fish/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 12:54:10 +0000</pubDate>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13176</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="8dc5d35ebd" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="2fcafe3d3d" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="654c1e66c3" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Bean Salad With Celery</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/bean-salad-with-celery/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 13:04:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13182</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="4fc33a6bd2" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="ccb57fb1b2" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="7c02cb9e51" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Appetizer Mussels</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/appetizer-mussels/</link>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="a1921f57e5" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="1aa777f17c" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="d5af8afaf8" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Bring to a boil and add mussels.";i:1;s:130:"Cover and continue to boil for about 4 to 6 minutes or until all the mussels have opened. Discard any mussels that haven't opened.";i:2;s:177:"Remove mussels from liquid and keep warm. Pour off liquid to leave about 1 cup. Try not to discard the garlic. Boil the 1 cup of liquid until it's reduced to about 3/4 of a cup.";i:3;s:103:"Add butter and stir until butter has melted and sauce has thickened slightly. 		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="9a118d84b2" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="e0b8cab3d7" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="949f7c9b2d" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Beer Cheese Dip</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/beer-cheese-dip/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 13:41:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13196</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="18518d11fe" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="b645bb863c" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="0605113c1c" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Reuben Sandwich</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/reuben-sandwich/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 13:47:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13199</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="203f515703" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="12565375ee" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="0460fdafac" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Pesto Cheese Sandwich</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/pesto-cheese-sandwich/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 13:50:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13202</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="5d372283fe" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="8b748d57ac" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="66b42f2544" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Strawberry Mojito</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/strawberry-mojito/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 13:59:58 +0000</pubDate>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13206</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="8a24be477c" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="417f75a3e5" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="1502625175" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Bloody Mary Cocktail</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/bloody-mary-cocktail/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 14:04:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13213</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="54bf1bee8f" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="1d7242c130" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="7bd2269404" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>The Real Mojito</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/the-real-mojito/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 29 Jun 2017 14:07:58 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13216</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="ee920c6d55" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="47b75e5366" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="9a999efcc4" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Party Lemonade</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/party-lemonade/</link>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="e5207a3977" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="d45978279c" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="ff5196f565" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>The Real Mojito</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/the-real-mojito-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:22:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13244</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="def1b4af65" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="3a6dfdfc67" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="76582da758" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Add 2 more lime wedges and the sugar, and muddle again to release the lime juice. Do not strain the mixture. Fill the glass almost to the top with ice. Pour the rum over the ice, and fill the glass with carbonated water. Stir, taste, and add more sugar if desired. Garnish with the remaining lime wedge.";}]]></wp:meta_value>

		<title>French Macaroon</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/french-macaroon-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:26:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13247</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="c22d1ef6c1" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="409e5ca0fa" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="610ceb3d90" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Sift confectioners' sugar and ground almonds in a separate bowl and quickly fold the almond mixture into the egg whites, about 30 strokes.";i:2;s:291:"Spoon a small amount of batter into a plastic bag with a small corner cut off and pipe a test disk of batter, about 1 1/2 inches in diameter, onto prepared baking sheet. If the disk of batter holds a peak instead of flattening immediately, gently fold the batter a few more times and retest.";i:3;s:308:"When batter is mixed enough to flatten immediately into an even disk, spoon into a pastry bag fitted with a plain round tip. Pipe the batter onto the baking sheet in rounds, leaving space between the disks. Let the piped cookies stand out at room temperature until they form a hard skin on top, about 1 hour.";i:4;s:46:"Preheat oven to 285 degrees F (140 degrees C).";i:5;s:101:"Bake cookies until set but not browned, about 10 minutes; let cookies cool completely before filling.";}]]></wp:meta_value>

		<title>Moroccan Shabbat Fish</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/moroccan-shabbat-fish-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:28:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13250</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="4da6ea9283" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="dd9fcfbc83" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="36b93591fd" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Pumpkin Ginger Cupcakes</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/pumpkin-ginger-cupcakes-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:30:27 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13253</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="86afd47b74" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="69caf5d5db" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="1475b29b10" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Whisk together the flour, pudding mix, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ground ginger, allspice, cloves, and crystallized ginger in a bowl; set aside.";i:1;s:425:"Beat the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar with an electric mixer in a large bowl until light and fluffy. The mixture should be noticeably lighter in color. Add the eggs one at a time, allowing each egg to blend into the butter mixture before adding the next. Beat in the vanilla and pumpkin puree with the last egg. Stir in the flour mixture, mixing until just incorporated. Pour the batter into the prepared muffin cups.";i:2;s:187:"Bake in the preheated oven until golden and the tops spring back when lightly pressed, about 20 minutes. Cool in the pans for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely on a wire rack.";}]]></wp:meta_value>

		<title>Strawberry Mojito</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/strawberry-mojito-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:32:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[backdoor]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13256</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="fdafb13824" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="7986466031" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="4239da3995" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Cras dapibus ullamcorper dictum. Vivamus nec erat placerat felis scelerisque porttitor in ac turpis. In nec imperdiet turpis. Suspendisse quis orci ut orci pulvinar eleifend. Nulla eu mattis ipsum. Integer eget sagittis nulla. Praesent consectetur lacus et maximus eleifend. Integer non lacus dui. Mauris tortor diam, laoreet quis commodo vitae, sodales vel augue.| Sed rutrum, libero non pretium tristique, arcu mi sollicitudin ex, quis venenatis orci tellus vel dolor. Donec gravida, dolor ut auctor facilisis, enim dolor pellentesque lectus, nec vehicula nibh risus ac leo. Mauris volutpat aliquam tellus nec rhoncus. Aliquam et nibh pulvinar, sodales nibh et, pretium urna. Vivamus quam augue, maximus in consequat imperdiet, iaculis non nibh. Aliquam erat volutpat. Curabitur venenatis massa sed lacus tristique, non auctor nisl sodales. Sed ultricies lacus ut libero faucibus fringilla. Ut nisi tellus, posuere vel mattis nec, convallis a metus. Nullam elementum molestie felis nec lobortis. Cras at justo eu elit semper tempor sed quis orci. In risus magna, malesuada vel elementum ut, finibus et nunc.

&nbsp;]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Turkey Sandwich</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/turkey-sandwich-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:33:56 +0000</pubDate>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13259</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="e8a5d508ec" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="6e4344662f" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="2d2a5af688" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="6823985e1a" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="1cc5c2336a" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="7982664955" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>

Lightly mix in the ground chuck, ground sirloin, onion soup mix, Worcestershire sauce, steak seasoning sauce, hot sauce, and salt and pepper. Form the meat mixture into 6 large patties, 6 inches across by 1 inch thick.";i:2;s:335:"Place the burgers on the preheated grill, and cook 10 to 15 minutes per side, until the burgers are browned and no longer pink in the middle. 		<title>Thai Buffalo Wings</title>
		<link>http://demo.good-food.cmsmasters.net/recipe/thai-buffalo-wings/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 07:41:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[cmsmasters]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://good-food.cmsmasters.net/?post_type=project&#038;p=13265</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[cmsmasters_row data_shortcode_id="c866509dbf" data_width="boxed" data_top_style="default" data_bot_style="default" data_color="default" data_padding_top="0" data_padding_bottom="0"][cmsmasters_column data_shortcode_id="555fafb85f" data_width="1/1"][cmsmasters_text shortcode_id="16a3383df2" animation_delay="0"]This blog resembles the pages of a glossy food magazine with a fleet of stylists making sure every bite looks impossibly scrumptious. But behind the scenes, there's just one incredible couple, Amy and Dylan Jameson. The division of labor is simple: She cooks and blogs; he photographs. The result elevates whole-food ingredients to epic proportions. Sandwiches, noodles, green salads, and other divine dishes have earned the attention of many in the food world, including magazine, which named Good Food one of the best original recipe blogs.[/cmsmasters_text][/cmsmasters_column][/cmsmasters_row]]]></content:encoded>
